16/01/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Resolving Kosovo's final status will not jeopardise security in the region, Romanian Defence Minister Sorin Frunzaverde and visiting Macedonian counterpart Lazar Elenovski agreed on Monday (January 15th). 
They stressed that regional co-operation is key to the Euro-Atlantic integration and stability of Southeast Europe.
The two ministers also agreed on a plan for Macedonian officers to undergo training at Romania's National Defence University. 
Elenovski told Frunzaverde that Macedonia is in the final stage of transforming its military, with the goal of meeting NATO standards. 
(Nine O'clock, Vecer - 16/01/07; MIA, Makfax, Telma TV - 15/01/07)
